1
00:00:08,858 --> 00:00:13,799
♪On a quiet night somewhere♪

2
00:00:15,825 --> 00:00:21,079
♪I longed
to hold your fading silhouette♪

3
00:00:21,920 --> 00:00:24,831
♪Yet my hands grasped only air♪

4
00:00:25,207 --> 00:00:28,341
♪Mocking my own persistence♪

5
00:00:29,127 --> 00:00:35,207
♪Turns out it was nothing but a dream♪

6
00:00:35,220 --> 00:00:41,876
♪Perhaps love
will blossom with the next spring♪

7
00:00:42,385 --> 00:00:45,520
♪Yet I can't help but feel the ache♪

8
00:00:45,636 --> 00:00:51,730
♪For you're no longer mine♪

9
00:00:52,741 --> 00:00:54,220
=Misaligned Lover=

10
00:00:54,220 --> 00:00:55,300
=Episode 14=

11
00:00:55,300 --> 00:00:56,872
(Adapted from
a Himalaya Qiji Literature novel)

12
00:00:56,872 --> 00:00:58,280
(Written by Xiang Bei, author
of Heard You Got a Dog Outside? Divorce!)

13
00:01:12,310 --> 00:01:14,080
If we hadn't broken up back then,

14
00:01:14,550 --> 00:01:16,920
would we still be together now?

15
00:01:17,270 --> 00:01:18,520
Maybe.

16
00:01:20,270 --> 00:01:21,640
Or maybe not.

17
00:01:22,430 --> 00:01:23,789
Because, Chen Zhiqing...

18
00:01:23,790 --> 00:01:26,400
You were always meant to be a superstar.

19
00:01:27,030 --> 00:01:28,400
Your light

20
00:01:28,710 --> 00:01:30,720
was never meant for just me.

21
00:02:13,550 --> 00:02:14,709
Zhiqing,

22
00:02:14,710 --> 00:02:16,749
we have a theatrical film project

23
00:02:16,750 --> 00:02:18,709
and would like to invite you
to play the lead role.

24
00:02:18,710 --> 00:02:20,229
I'll send you the project details.

25
00:02:20,230 --> 00:02:21,269
Take a look first.

26
00:02:21,270 --> 00:02:22,360
All right.

27
00:03:09,510 --> 00:03:11,680
Why are you leaving so soon?

28
00:03:14,470 --> 00:03:17,640
If I say I walked into the wrong room,
would you believe me?

29
00:03:24,670 --> 00:03:26,720
Is it really just a mistake?

30
00:03:28,550 --> 00:03:29,789
It is.

31
00:03:29,790 --> 00:03:32,280
Nothing happened between us.

32
00:03:40,150 --> 00:03:42,080
Then what's with the mark on your neck?

33
00:03:45,270 --> 00:03:46,909
We're adults.

34
00:03:46,910 --> 00:03:49,520
Some things don't need
to be taken too seriously.

35
00:03:49,910 --> 00:03:52,949
What? "Adults don't need
to take it seriously"?

36
00:03:52,950 --> 00:03:54,360
What do you mean by that?

37
00:03:55,470 --> 00:03:57,469
Why are you getting so worked up?

38
00:03:57,470 --> 00:03:59,480
I never said you
had to take responsibility.

39
00:04:06,870 --> 00:04:08,080
Where's Mr. Yan?

40
00:04:08,310 --> 00:04:09,440
He took a cab.

41
00:04:20,270 --> 00:04:22,120
What's going on with that couple now?

42
00:04:39,270 --> 00:04:41,320
What's going on between you and Mr. Yan?

43
00:04:41,590 --> 00:04:42,600
Nothing.

44
00:04:43,270 --> 00:04:45,320
Then why has he been staring
at you the whole way?

45
00:04:47,510 --> 00:04:48,920
Maybe his eyes have issues.

46
00:04:51,550 --> 00:04:54,960
No way. Something is definitely
going on between you two.

47
00:05:01,490 --> 00:05:03,469
(Artist Rest Area)
Our story

48
00:05:03,470 --> 00:05:05,629
is mainly about responsibility.

49
00:05:05,630 --> 00:05:07,560
Whether for one's country or for love,

50
00:05:07,830 --> 00:05:09,149
as a man,

51
00:05:09,150 --> 00:05:11,520
one should have the courage
to take responsibility.

52
00:05:12,590 --> 00:05:15,720
So just because we're adults, does that mean
we don't have to take responsibility?

53
00:05:21,150 --> 00:05:22,000
Well...

54
00:05:22,310 --> 00:05:23,560
What is it?

55
00:05:23,590 --> 00:05:24,669
Really?

56
00:05:24,670 --> 00:05:25,709
Are you sure?

57
00:05:25,710 --> 00:05:27,800
Of course. They already
called me from their side.

58
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,480
- They want you for the role.
- They called?

59
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:30,880
I also think you're the perfect fit.

60
00:05:31,310 --> 00:05:32,269
Really?

61
00:05:32,270 --> 00:05:33,069
Yeah.

62
00:05:33,070 --> 00:05:34,400
I'm a perfect fit?

63
00:05:41,350 --> 00:05:42,280
Come here.

64
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:43,800
What?

65
00:05:47,270 --> 00:05:50,360
Mu Chenxi, why are you
not taking responsibility for me?

66
00:05:55,830 --> 00:05:56,880
No...

67
00:05:58,310 --> 00:06:00,680
Let's talk about this later, all right?

68
00:06:03,990 --> 00:06:05,789
Are you dissatisfied

69
00:06:05,790 --> 00:06:07,200
with my performance last night?

70
00:06:13,270 --> 00:06:14,709
Playing it this bold, huh?

71
00:06:14,710 --> 00:06:15,789
From now on,

72
00:06:15,790 --> 00:06:17,560
Mu Chenxi is our top star.

73
00:06:17,830 --> 00:06:19,000
Okay.

74
00:06:20,150 --> 00:06:21,149
Minister Cheng,

75
00:06:21,150 --> 00:06:23,480
has the male lead
for the new project been decided?

76
00:06:24,070 --> 00:06:26,720
The company wants you
to work with Zhiqing again.

77
00:06:26,790 --> 00:06:29,600
But a theatrical film
specifically requested him.

78
00:06:29,750 --> 00:06:30,869
The director is well-known,

79
00:06:30,870 --> 00:06:33,000
so it's hard to turn down.

80
00:06:33,470 --> 00:06:34,909
But the company

81
00:06:34,910 --> 00:06:37,029
is already arranging
a new co-star for you.

82
00:06:37,030 --> 00:06:38,920
It should be settled soon.

83
00:06:39,790 --> 00:06:41,560
I have a good candidate.

84
00:06:43,630 --> 00:06:44,600
Who?

85
00:06:45,870 --> 00:06:47,349
Yan Lidong.

86
00:06:47,350 --> 00:06:50,280
A new actor under Xitu Entertainment.

87
00:06:50,870 --> 00:06:52,029
That might not work.

88
00:06:52,030 --> 00:06:53,189
Why?

89
00:06:53,190 --> 00:06:54,560
He doesn't have the availability.

90
00:06:54,790 --> 00:06:56,189
His company lined up

91
00:06:56,190 --> 00:06:57,600
a major S+ project for him.

92
00:06:58,590 --> 00:07:00,000
Has the female lead been confirmed?

93
00:07:00,030 --> 00:07:00,840
Yes.

94
00:07:00,990 --> 00:07:03,869
Apparently,

95
00:07:03,870 --> 00:07:05,960
